cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper discusses the usage practices and limitations of mobile translation tools, which are related to natural language processing and human-computer interaction (cs.CL and cs.HC). The studies conducted in the paper involve populations spanning socioeconomic status and geographic regions, which could fall under the categories of computational sociology (cs.CY), social informatics (cs.SI), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
